<body>

  <h1>StrideX E-Commerce Full Site Creation Guide</h1>
  <p>This document serves as a complete blueprint to build the StrideX Premium Sports Shoes E-Commerce website from scratch, incorporating responsive mobile features and the functional wishlist page.</p>

  <h2>1. Project Overview & Architecture</h2>
  <p>StrideX is a high-performance athletic footwear e-commerce platform built with clean, premium design aesthetics (glassmorphism, vibrant accents, dark mode components, and micro-animations) using <strong>HTML5</strong>, <strong>CSS3</strong>, and <strong>Vanilla Javascript</strong>.</p>

  <h3>Project Directory Structure</h3>
  <pre>Sport/
├── index.html                   # Landing/Home Page
├── package.json                 # Project configuration & npx http-server script
├── css/
│   ├── styles.css               # Imports reset, variables, layout, components
│   ├── reset.css                # CSS Reset normalization rules
│   ├── variables.css            # Color palette tokens, fonts, spacing values
│   ├── layout.css               # Global container, site header/footer structures
│   ├── components.css           # Buttons, form controls, product card skeletons
│   └── pages/
│       ├── landing.css          # Landing-specific animations and best sellers slider
│       ├── products.css         # Catalog page, grid layouts, filters, quick view
│       ├── detail.css           # Gallery, spec table, accordions, sticky buy bar
│       └── cart.css             # Shopping cart item rows, checkout summary grid
├── js/
│   ├── app.js                   # Smooth scrolling reveal logic
│   ├── data.js                  # Products database array
│   ├── state.js                 # LocalStorage cart management state
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── Header.js            # Header rendering, slide-out drawer, wishlist badge
│   │   └── Footer.js            # Footer rendering, social links
│   └── pages/
│       ├── landing.js           # Home page slideshow bindings
│       ├── products.js          # Filtering, sorting, wishlist toggling, quick view
│       ├── detail.js            # Gallery swatches, bundle builder, related products
│       ├── cart.js              # Checkout summaries, save for later lists
│       └── wishlist.js          # Wishlist items display and cart integrations
└── pages/
    ├── products.html            # Shop listing page
    ├── product-detail.html      # Product specifications details page
    ├── cart.html                # Cart page
    └── wishlist.html            # Wishlist items page</pre>

  <h2>2. Setup & Installation (Day 1 - Tomorrow)</h2>
  
  <h3>Step 1: Project Initialization</h3>
  <p>Initialize <code>package.json</code> to configure the dev server script:</p>
  <pre>{
  "name": "stridex-sports-shoes",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Premium Sports Shoes Ecommerce website built with HTML5, CSS3, and Vanilla JS.",
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "npx http-server -p 3000"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "http-server": "^14.1.1"
  }
}</pre>
  <p>Run the following commands in the project terminal to install dependencies and run the server:</p>
  <pre>npm install
npm run dev</pre>

  <h3>Step 2: Global Design System Configuration (<code>variables.css</code>)</h3>
  <p>Configure the brand tokens:</p>
  <pre>:root {
  --primary: #0055ff;
  --secondary: #ffb100;
  --bg-main: #f8f9fa;
  --bg-card: #ffffff;
  --border-color: #e5e7eb;
  --text-primary: #111827;
  --text-secondary: #4b5563;
  --text-muted: #9ca3af;
  --radius-sm: 4px;
  --radius-md: 8px;
  --radius-lg: 16px;
  --z-header: 100;
  --z-modal: 200;
  --font-display: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
  --transition-normal: 0.3s;
  --transition-fast: 0.15s;
}</pre>

  <h2>3. Step-by-Step Implementation Timeline</h2>

  <h3>Phase 1: Shared Core Modules (Day 1)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Write <code>data.js</code> containing product records with availability, price, reviews count, colors, sizes, and specs.</li>
    <li>Write <code>state.js</code> to manage operations like <code>addToCart()</code>, <code>removeFromCart()</code>, and <code>saveCart()</code> synced with <code>localStorage</code>.</li>
    <li>Write <code>Header.js</code> to dynamically inject the global nav bar, slide-out cart drawer, and live badge updates for the cart and wishlist.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Phase 2: Catalog Page & Slide-Out Filters (Day 2)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Build <code>products.html</code> and <code>products.js</code> to bind category, size, price range slider, color, and rating filters.</li>
    <li>Design the mobile sliding filters panel in <code>products.css</code>:
      <ul>
        <li>Translate the sidebar off-screen (<code>translateX(100%)</code>) on screens &lt; 992px.</li>
        <li>Add transition rules to slide it into view (<code>translateX(0)</code>) when the <code>.active</code> class is applied.</li>
        <li>Implement a blurred backdrop layer (<code>.filter-overlay</code>) that closes the filter drawer when clicked.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Phase 3: Detail Page & Interactive Sliders (Day 3)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Build <code>product-detail.html</code> and <code>detail.js</code> to show the zoom-on-hover gallery, swatches, and sizes selectors.</li>
    <li>Build the <strong>Related Products slider</strong>:
      <ul>
        <li>Structure the slider track with <code>.slider-container-outer</code> and <code>.slider-track</code> containing cards sized with <code>flex: 0 0 300px</code>.</li>
        <li>Bind smooth <code>scrollBy()</code> scrolling rules to previous/next navigation buttons.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Build the <strong>Frequently Bought Together</strong> section:
      <ul>
        <li>Stack the bundle items checkboxes on top and the total bundle price summary column at the bottom vertically on viewports &lt; 768px.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Build the <strong>Mobile Sticky Buy Bar</strong>:
      <ul>
        <li>Show a fixed bar at the bottom containing only the price and the "Add to Cart" action button when viewport screen sizes are &lt; 576px.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Phase 4: Cart Row Optimizations & Wishlist Page (Day 4)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Optimize the cart item row layout in <code>cart.css</code> for mobile screens (&lt; 576px):
      <ul>
        <li>Apply grid areas (<code>info info info</code>, <code>qty price total</code>) to place columns side-by-side.</li>
        <li>Use <code>::before</code> pseudo-elements to cleanly display "Price" and "Total" labels above their values.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Build <code>wishlist.html</code> and <code>wishlist.js</code> to show saved shoes, sync items with localStorage, remove saved cards dynamically, and quick-add favorites directly into the shopping cart.</li>
  </ul>

